Kowloon's documentation teams have confirmed what the Conclave records described: the Bellspine Resonance Anchor Construct is the central monitoring intelligence that has been running the anchor network continuously since the Conclave's collapse. It is not simply a recording device; it has been actively discharging accumulated crystalline resonance energy as lethal pulses to prevent access to its data core. The Jade Magistracy has authorized a decommission order: the Construct's institutional function ended when the Conclave did, and the geological record it holds belongs to all cities, not a defunct institution.
The Anchor Construct has been decommissioned and Kowloon's documentation teams have accessed the data core for the first time. What they found has been classified at the highest Jade Magistracy level: three centuries of uninterrupted geological data showing the Ember Crown is building toward a major eruption cycle at a rate that existing models significantly underestimated. The Magistracy is convening an emergency session to determine the intercity compact obligations when one city holds the only data set proving continent-wide geological risk.
